docs/api-reference.md:1561:Sets the simulation speed multiplier for the real-time loop. `2` means ticks accumulate twice as fast. `0.5` means half speed. Has no effect on `step()`.
docs/api-reference.md:1592:Resumes the real-time loop at the current speed multiplier. Resets the time accumulator to prevent a burst of ticks.
docs/api-reference.md:1604:Commands are validated-and-queued input from external code (AI agents, UI). They are processed at the start of each tick, before spatial sync and systems.
docs/api-reference.md:1687:Sets the handler for a command type. Exactly one handler per type. The handler runs at tick start when commands are processed.
docs/api-reference.md:1691:When a command is processed but no handler is registered, the tick fails with a structured `TickFailure`. `world.step()` surfaces that failure as `WorldTickFailureError`. `ClientAdapter` checks this ahead of time and rejects unhandled client commands before they enter the queue.
