docs/changelog.md:126:- `worldWidth`, `worldHeight`, `blockSize` must be **safe positive integers** (`Number.isSafeInteger`). The constructor also rejects `width * height` products that exceed `Number.MAX_SAFE_INTEGER`.
docs/changelog.md-127-- `defaultValue` and every written cell value must satisfy `assertJsonCompatible` — no functions, symbols, BigInt, circular references, or class instances.
docs/changelog.md-128-- Cell coordinates must be integers in `[0, width)` × `[0, height)`; world coordinates must be integers in `[0, worldWidth)` × `[0, worldHeight)`. Both out-of-range and non-integer inputs throw `RangeError` (consistent error type).
